A Florida teen is fighting for her life after she was stabbed multiple times by a registered sex offender during a police chase.

Ashley Lyon, 16, from Valrico, went missing Friday, with her parents believing she was lured away by 41-year-old Steven Patrick Myers, who has twice been convicted of child molestation.

The pair were spotted at the Tiger Truck Stop near Grosse Tete, Louisiana, at about midnight Wednesday by a patron who recognized them from an Amber Alert.

