The patron called the Iberville Sheriff's deputies who arrived to find Lyon and Myers in a Chevy 3500 flatbed pickup truck.

When Myers, who was driving, spotted the deputies he fled in the truck and a high speed chase ensued that stretched more than 40 miles to Lafayette, authorities said.Â 

Myers rammed four other cars during the chase, in what appeared to be an attempt to create roadblocks behind him.

According to the Tampa Bay Times, stop sticks eventually deflated his tires, however the criminal continued driving until his tires wore down to the rims.

